{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a69417cc3fb48d67033", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "615d92edde3d91842a5cf813", "title": "JEE Main 2021 (18 Mar Shift 2)", "isVisible": true}], "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 1, "approximateTimeRequired": 120, "question": {"text": "<p>Three rays of light, namely red <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>R</mi></mfenced></math>,&nbsp;green <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>G</mi><mo>)</mo></math> and blue <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></math> are incident on the face <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>Q</mi></math> of a right angled prism <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>Q</mi><mi>R</mi></math>&nbsp;as shown in figure.</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/ced3db70-d3eb-4121-a996-ca3d025ed244-image.png\" style=\"width: 288px; height: 189px;\" /></p><p>The refractive indices of the material of the&nbsp;prism for red, green and blue wavelength are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>27</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>42</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>49</mn></math> respectively. The colour of the ray(s) emerging out of the face <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>R</mi></math> is :</p>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "8LZBW", "text": "green", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "nFVTZ", "text": "red", "isCorrect": true, "image": null}, {"id": "H1GwD", "text": "blue and green", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "cFHdn", "text": "blue", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/2e32dc80-263a-4ca9-86ef-2de73b67cc5b-image.png\" style=\"width: 311px; height: 221px;\" /></p><p>Assuming that the right angled prism is an isoceles prism, so the other angles will be <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math> each.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo></math> Each incident ray will make an angle of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math> with the normal at face <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>R</mi></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo></math> The wavelength corresponding to which the incidence angle is less than the critical angle, will pass through <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>R</mi></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>&#952;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub><mo>=</mo></math> critical angle</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>&#952;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo></math> If <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>&#952;</mi><mi>C</mi></msub><mo>&#8805;</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p>the light ray will pass</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mfenced><msub><mi>&#952;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub></mfenced><mi>Red</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>27</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>51</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>94</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p>Red will pass.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mfenced><msub><mi>&#952;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub></mfenced><mi>Green</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>42</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>44</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>76</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p>Green will not pass</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mfenced><msub><mi>&#952;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub></mfenced><mi>Blue</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>49</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>42</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p>Blue will not pass</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo></math> So only red will pass through <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>R</mi></math>.</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "questionLabels": [], "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ61491264", "source": "EM", "bucket": "Must Do Ques (JEE Main) - Any Difficulty", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "category": null, "microConcepts": [], "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564d